This is the worst rental experience we have had. They will repair minor things but nothing important. We had a bathroom flood, not fault of our own, back in September of 2024. I have been patient working to get the company to fix the bathroom flooring that was coming up after that. They claimed they needed to wait until insurance payed out. Several months later insurance paid and all they did was a cosmetic patch on the ceiling‚Ä¶water poured through our kitchen chandelier and multiple places in our ceiling from the flood. When it happened I contact emergency maintenance but they did not consider it an emergency. We bought a carpet cleaning machine to suck water out of the carpets and cleaned up the best we could. The maintenance company has came to look at the flooring several times, they want to fix it. However then property management company refused to approve the repairs needed. Our kitchen floor is peeling up. I have to place a mat over it so we don‚Äôt trip.

We notified that we will not be resigning our lease due to them not fixing things. Our lease is up July 31st. I just accepted they are hard to work with so will just deal with the issues and not resign. They are already wanting to do showings (60 days before lease is up) and are not willing to ask me times that work. We are working parents and have minors home while at work. I keep voicing I do not feel comfortable with them coming to our home with only minors there. They remind me they have a key so we don‚Äôt need to be there, that doesn‚Äôt address the issue! They have already scheduled 2 showing without asking if the time works. I politely asked for weekend days because minors won‚Äôt be home alone. They continue to schedule on weekdays.

I wanted to be polite and amicable due to needing a good reference for finding a new rental but they are being impossible to work with. I usually don‚Äôt write bad reviews but I am at my wits ends. They ignore all my concerns.

Real Property Management Utah County was by far the most difficult rental company we‚Äôve ever dealt with. Throughout our year-long lease, they consistently failed to communicate, delayed maintenance requests by weeks (if they responded at all), and treated us like an inconvenience rather than tenants.

At move-out, they refused to let us walk through the property and withheld over $600 from our deposit for completely unreasonable charges‚Äîincluding $200 for lightbulbs, when only a few were out. Our lease didn‚Äôt say anything about needing to replace bulbs, but had we known they'd charge triple digits for them, we obviously would‚Äôve handled it ourselves.

They also tried to charge us $1,500 for a broken garage door we didn‚Äôt break, and it became clear that their goal was to stick tenants with upgrade costs so they could flip the home for resale. It felt dishonest and predatory.

Lisa, the manager, speaks to tenants in a condescending tone and was consistently rude during conversations. Bethany, the assistant manager, rarely listened and dismissed our concerns without resolution. Their behavior made it clear that tenant experience is not their priority‚Äîmoney and control are.

I wouldn‚Äôt recommend Real Property Management Utah County to anyone. Be cautious, document EVERYTHING, and if you can, avoid renting through them altogether.

RPM took over my lease from a previous property management company. The previous management company was terrible. In contrast,  RPM was always courteous and responsive to my inquiries and requests.  They were assertive in following up with the homeowner regarding maintenance requests for the rental property. Bethany, my property manager was excellent.  She was always courteous, knowledgeable and responsive.  She was able to get several maintenance issues resolved that had been lagging for months.

Terrible service! The people who run this have zero respect for the tenants. They refused to give a detailed list of things that they kept money for when we moved out. They claimed it was NECESSARY to pay $300 for professional cleaning (800 sq ft place) because they saw a shelf with crumbs. They wouldn‚Äôt tell us the company that went out to clean so we could confirm. We had pics and that place was so much nicer than when we first rented it. And the funny thing is is they used pictures from ANOTHER property for proof. It wasn‚Äôt even our place. They used pics from another rental AND used old pictures from past inspections. We took pictures after TWO DAYS of cleaning and they came became with the pics and none of it matched up. When we asked for more details and for more proof they refused. So $300 for a professional crumb clean up (??!?) They gave us nickels and times back from our deposit and we fought as much as we could. Terrible service. Multiple times we had issues and NEVER did we get them fixed. Like snow and rain blowing in the front door. They wouldn‚Äôt respond or they wouldn‚Äôt send anyone. These people don‚Äôt care they just want to pocket your money. Which the owners who were using them even believed too after we contacted them about the terrible service. I know they might respond and try and cover themselves, but that‚Äôs what they do. I‚Äôve read reviews and agree 10000%. They are liars and will steal your money for themselves.

Amazing property management company. They were so incredible and accommodating when I moved into my new rental and I absolutely love my rental. I submitted a maintenance request and they came in the same day and fixed it super professional. Everyone there  is so kind Absolutely have loved living here so far and I‚Äôm excited to continue renting from them. Highly recommend this company to everybody!

detailedReviews.author: Samantha
detailedReviews.text:
Your home will not be rented, you will lose money, time and owe fees for their terrible work.  Teri, Lisa, Cassidy are not qualified to be property managers.  I lost over 5k in rent, and more...

The worst property management service I have ever used to get my home rented. Here is a quick recap of what you can expect if you use them:
- Home was not rented - I waited 3 months
- Even though I asked, advertisements were not ran
- I had to call in to get updates, and the team was annoyed when I asked what was going on
- Original receipts for performed work were not provided, and unclear markups were applied without proper documentation.
- Unauthorized work was conducted beyond the initially approved budget.
- Despite our agreed-upon parting without fees, I later received a collection notice demanding over $1,000.

This entire experience was not only financially burdensome but also incredibly frustrating due to the failure on their part to fulfill basic responsibilities. After they were fired my new property manager had a renter in there in 1 week, highlighting a significant difference in performance.

detailedReviews.text: I've been renting with RPM a little over 2 years now. I've rented on my own for about 6 in total and RPM IS BY FAR THE BEST. I really hope I am going to be able to renew my lease for a few more years. RPM, though, has made it so easy these past few years! Not to mention, they have an amazing option when paying your rent to have it reported to the credit bureau. Thank you so much RPM!

detailedReviews.text: These guys are simply the best. Hands down. What you need in property management is a company you can trust to take care of your investment and that you can count on to get the job done. I've worked with Teri and it's like having someone who cares as much as I do about the properties I purchased. She is quick to respond, thorough and she knows her business backwards and forwards. She has the team to deliver, and she has people who trust her. It's easy to see why you could operate an army with Teri in charge. I cannot recommend them highly enough.

detailedReviews.author: Emily Frisina
detailedReviews.text: Raquel was very helpful in our recent payment for rent. I got paid a day later than the 5 day window and we had to choose between paying rent on time or getting the food we needed and paying other bills. I asked RPM for a one day extension as a one time courtesy since we had been paying on time for 2 years without asking for anything in the past. Raquel quickly replied, confirmed we could and then informed me to reach out once the payment was made so that the fees were reversed. As soon as I made the payment, I messaged back and within 30 minutes Raquel worked with accounting to get the fees taken care of. This relieved a lot of stress for us this month and we truly appreciate RPM & Raquel working with us on this one time issue.

detailedReviews.author: Briettny Curtner
detailedReviews.text: Raquel has been transparent, helpful, and trusting  since the start! Trying to find a home during the holidays was tedious, however, Raquel made her self available. Now, we await our application results! Thank you Raquel, we wouldn't be one step closer to our dream home if it was not for you!

negative.author: Megan & Preston Meldrum
negative.text:
Real Property Management Utah County was by far the most difficult rental company we‚Äôve ever dealt with. Throughout our year-long lease, they consistently failed to communicate, delayed maintenance requests by weeks (if they responded at all), and treated us like an inconvenience rather than tenants.

At move-out, they refused to let us walk through the property and withheld over $600 from our deposit for completely unreasonable charges‚Äîincluding $200 for lightbulbs, when only a few were out. Our lease didn‚Äôt say anything about needing to replace bulbs, but had we known they'd charge triple digits for them, we obviously would‚Äôve handled it ourselves.

They also tried to charge us $1,500 for a broken garage door we didn‚Äôt break, and it became clear that their goal was to stick tenants with upgrade costs so they could flip the home for resale. It felt dishonest and predatory.

Lisa, the manager, speaks to tenants in a condescending tone and was consistently rude during conversations. Bethany, the assistant manager, rarely listened and dismissed our concerns without resolution. Their behavior made it clear that tenant experience is not their priority‚Äîmoney and control are.

I wouldn‚Äôt recommend Real Property Management Utah County to anyone. Be cautious, document EVERYTHING, and if you can, avoid renting through them altogether.
